1. To use the ribbon commands, what menu and grouping of commands will you find the Insert and Delete command?
Under the Home tab we will find a ribbon grouping called Cells there we will find Insert and Delete command.

2. If you set a row height or column width to 0 (zero), what happens to the row and
column?
If I set a row height or column width to 0 (zero),It sets to the default width or height.

3. Is there a need to change the height and width in a cell? Why?
Yes,there is a need to change the height and width in a cell.Because,when we typing a lengthy paragraph we need to change the height and width in a cell
so that it can fit the data.

4. What is the keyboard shortcut to unhide rows?
The keyboard shortcut to unhide rows is Ctrl + Shift + 9.

5. How to hide rows containing blank cells?
Step-1- Select the range that contains empty cells you want to hide.
Step-2- On the Home tab, in the Editing group, click Find & Select > Go To Special.
Step-3- In the Go To Special dialog box, select the Blanks radio button, and click OK. This will select all empty cells in the range.
Step-4- Press Ctrl + 9 to hide the corresponding rows.

6. What are the steps to hide the duplicate values using conditional formatting in
excel?
The steps to hide the duplicate values using conditional formatting in
excel: click Data > Data Tools > Remove Duplicates. 


